===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|linguistics|lang=en}} A higher-pitched or stronger [[articulation]] of a particular [[syllable]] of a word or phrase in order to [[distinguish]] it from the others or to [[emphasize]] it.
#: ''In the word "careful", the '''accent''' is placed on the first syllable.''
# {{context|figuratively|lang=en}} Emphasis or importance in general.
#: ''At this hotel, the '''accent''' is on luxury.''
# {{context|orthography|lang=en}} A [[mark]] or [[character]] used in writing, in order to indicate the place of the [[spoken]] accent, or to indicate the nature or quality of the vowel marked.
#: ''The name Cézanne is written with an acute '''accent'''.''
# {{senseid|en|modulation of the voice}}{{context|linguistics|lang=en}} [[modulation|Modulation]] of the voice in speaking; the manner of speaking or pronouncing; a peculiar or characteristic modification of the voice, expressing emotion; [[tone]].
#: ''a foreign '''accent'''; a French or a German '''accent'''''
#* '''1608''', [[w:William Shakespeare|William Shakespeare]], ''[[w:King Lear|King Lear]]'', II-ii
#*: I know, sir, I am no flatterer: he that beguiled you in a plain '''accent''' was a plain knave; which for my part I will not be, though I should win your displeasure to entreat me to 't.
#* '''1696''', [[w: Matthew Prior|Matthew Prior]], "From Celia to Damon", in ''Poems on Several Occasions''
#*: The tender '''Accent''' of a Woman's Cry / Will pass unheard, will unregarded die;
# A [[word]]; a significant [[tone]] or [[sound]].
# {{context|usually|plural only|lang=en}} Expressions in general; [[speech]].
#* Dryden
#*: Winds! on your wings to Heaven her '''accents''' bear, / Such words as Heaven alone is fit to hear.
# {{context|prosody|poetry|lang=en}} Stress laid on certain syllables of a [[verse]].
# {{context|music|lang=en}} A regularly [[recur]]ring [[stress]] upon the tone to mark the beginning, and, more feebly, the third part of the [[measure]].
# {{context|music|lang=en}} A special [[emphasis]] of a tone, even in the weaker part of the measure.
# {{context|music|lang=en}} The rhythmical accent, which marks [[phrase]]s and [[section]]s of a [[period]].
# {{context|music|lang=en}} The [[expressive]] emphasis and [[shading]] of a passage.
#: {{rfquotek|J. S. Dwight}}
# {{context|music|lang=en}} A mark used to represent specific stress on a note.
# {{context|mathematics|lang=en}} A mark placed at the right hand of a [[letter]], and a little above it, to distinguish [[magnitude]]s of a similar kind expressed by the same letter, but differing in value, as '''y'''', '''y<nowiki>''</nowiki>'''.
# {{context|geometry|lang=en}} A mark at the right hand of a number, indicating [[minute]]s of a [[degree]], [[second]]s, etc., as in '''12' 27<nowiki>''</nowiki>''', meaning twelve minutes and twenty-seven seconds.
# {{context|engineering|lang=en}} A mark used to denote [[feet]] and [[inch]]es, as in '''6' 10<nowiki>''</nowiki>''', meaning six feet ten inches.
# Emphasis laid on a part of an artistic design or composition; an emphasized detail, in particular a detail in sharp contrast to its surroundings.
# A very small gemstone set into a piece of jewellery.
# A distinctive feature or quality.
# {{context|archaic|lang=en}} [[utterance|Utterance]].

